\title{fireregimetools: Tools for Summarizing Fire Regime Statistics From Simulations}
\description{
Memory-bounded, Arrow-native summaries of simulated fire regimes. Per-replicate fire-size and annual-area-burned tables are written to partitioned parquet and reduced across replicates by pushing the aggregation down to Arrow compute (so the per-replicate rows are never all held in memory at once), plus a fire-size distribution plot. Companion to nrvtools for the fire side of natural-range-of-variation post-processing.
